WEBVTT

00:05.573 --> 00:09.009
- None of your
business, Elaine!
- ( audience laughs )

00:10.078 --> 00:12.113
- All: No!
- ( theme music playing )

00:22.256 --> 00:25.025
- OH, SORRY ABOUT THAT.
- A RING STAIN?

00:25.126 --> 00:27.995
I HAVE A BAD HABIT
OF JUST PUTTING MY DRINK
DOWN ON THE TABLE.

00:28.096 --> 00:30.698
BAD HABIT?
PUT YOUR DRINK DOWN
ON THE WOOD?

00:30.798 --> 00:34.502
- LOOK AT THAT STAIN YOU MADE.
- WELL, WE'LL JUST SAND IT
OFF OR SOMETHING.

00:37.171 --> 00:39.340
DO YOU RESPECT WOOD?

00:42.310 --> 00:44.612
I--

00:44.712 --> 00:46.280
- GUESS SO.
- OH MY GOD.

00:46.380 --> 00:48.916
YOU HAD A CUP LIKE THAT
AT JULIA'S PARTY.

00:49.016 --> 00:51.619
YOU LEFT THE RING STAIN
ON JULIA'S TABLE.

00:51.719 --> 00:54.088
SHE BLAMED ME
THE WHOLE TIME,
BUT IT WAS YOU.

00:54.188 --> 00:56.657
- WELL, IT'S NO BIG DEAL.
- YOU'RE RIGHT.

00:56.757 --> 00:58.626
IT IS NO BIG DEAL.

00:58.726 --> 01:01.562
HAVING SAID THAT,

01:01.662 --> 01:04.765
I WOULD LOVE FOR YOU
TO CALL JULIA AND TELL HER
YOU LEFT THE RING STAIN.

01:04.865 --> 01:06.934
- I'M NOT CALLING JULIA.
- YEAH, JUST TELL HER THAT--

01:07.034 --> 01:09.503
THAT YOU WERE THE ONE
WHO LEFT THE STAIN
ON THE ANTIQUE TABLE.

01:09.603 --> 01:11.272
- HOLD IT ONE SECOND.
- I'M NOT GONNA DO THAT.

01:11.372 --> 01:12.873
- YEAH, COME ON.
- I'M NOT DOING THAT.

01:12.973 --> 01:15.243
- NO, I WANT YOU TO TALK TO HER.
- I DON'T WANT TO TALK TO JULIA.

01:15.343 --> 01:19.513
- CHERYL, HOLD ON ONE SECOND.
- OH MY GOD, I AM NOT TALKING
TO JULIA.

01:19.613 --> 01:21.615
- I'M NOT DOING THIS.
- HEY, JULES!

01:21.715 --> 01:24.952
- SHOW WAS FANTASTIC.
- WHAT WAS I THINKING?
WHY WOULD I COME HERE?

01:25.052 --> 01:27.455
I'M NOT TALKING TO JULIA.
I SAID NO

01:27.555 --> 01:29.190
AND YOU DON'T
LISTEN TO ME.

01:29.290 --> 01:31.058
OH WAIT, HOLD--
HOLD ON, OKAY.

01:31.159 --> 01:34.061
CHERYL, WAIT ONE SECOND!
NO NO, I THINK SHE LEFT
THE RING STAIN. HOLD ON.

01:34.162 --> 01:37.231
- HEY, WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?
- LEAVING, LARRY.

01:37.331 --> 01:39.733
- HUH? WHY?
- WHY?!

01:39.833 --> 01:41.602
YEAH.
CHERYL!

01:41.702 --> 01:44.472
CHERYL.

01:47.175 --> 01:49.810
( theme music playing )

01:55.916 --> 01:59.052
Man: LARRY, I KNOW DIVORCE
IS PAINFUL, BUT THIS IS
A FANTASTIC DEAL.

01:59.153 --> 02:01.322
IT'S NOT ONLY THE BEST DEAL
I'M GONNA GET FOR YOU,

02:01.422 --> 02:03.090
IT'S THE BEST DEAL THAT
ANYBODY'S GONNA GET FOR ANYBODY.

02:03.191 --> 02:05.259
YOU'RE GONNA KEEP YOUR HOUSE,
YOU'RE KEEPING ALL
YOUR PROPERTY.

02:05.359 --> 02:07.161
YOU KNOW?
I KNOW THAT'S
IMPORTANT TO YOU.

02:07.261 --> 02:09.830
- I GOTTA BE A GOOD GUY.
- YEAH, YOU WILL LOOK LIKE
A GOOD GUY HERE.

02:09.930 --> 02:12.166
- BUT I DON'T REALLY WANT
TO BE A GOOD GUY HERE.
- I KNOW.

02:12.266 --> 02:14.067
- YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?
- YES.

02:14.168 --> 02:15.769
- OKAY, YEAH.
- THIS IS WHAT I DO.

02:15.869 --> 02:19.373
YOU'RE COMING OUT AHEAD
IN THIS DEAL AND SHE'S
COMING OUT BEHIND.

02:19.473 --> 02:21.575
IMAGINE LIKE A DUTCH
APPLE PIE, RIGHT?

02:21.675 --> 02:25.045
THE FILLING, THE REAL MEAT
OF THE PIE, IS EVERYTHING
YOU'RE GETTING.

02:25.145 --> 02:27.648
AND THE TOP OF THE PIE
THAT LOOKS SO NICE

02:27.748 --> 02:30.318
IS WHAT SHE'S GETTING.
SHE'S JUST GETTING
THE APPEARANCE.

02:30.418 --> 02:33.321
YEAH, BUT I REALLY LIKE
THAT CRUMBLY STUFF ON THE TOP.

02:33.421 --> 02:35.356
NO, EVERYBODY DOES.
YEAH, IT'S DELICIOUS.

02:35.456 --> 02:38.192
I LIKE THAT MORE THAN THE PIE.
I WOULD RATHER GET THAT

02:38.292 --> 02:41.195
- THAN THE PIE.
- YEAH, I KNOW, BUT IT'S--

02:41.295 --> 02:43.431
BUT THAT'S JUST--
THAT'S A PART OF IT,

02:43.531 --> 02:45.766
BUT THE REAL-- IT WOULDN'T BE
A PIE WITHOUT THE FILLING.

02:45.866 --> 02:48.101
- YEAH, BUT IT'S
MY FAVORITE PART.
- SO LET'S SWITCH IT.

02:48.202 --> 02:51.439
SHE'S GETTING
THE FILLING AND YOU'RE GETTING
THE RAZZLE-DAZZLE THAT IS

02:51.539 --> 02:54.041
- THE BROWN CRUMBLY STUFF.
- THE DELICIOUS BROWN
CRUMBLY STUFF.

02:54.141 --> 02:55.476
- YEAH, YEAH YEAH.
- THE CINNAMON.

02:55.576 --> 02:57.278
IT'S A GOOD DEAL.
IT'S READY TO BE SIGNED.

02:57.378 --> 02:58.979
EVERYTHING'S GOING
TO BE FINE, LARRY.

02:59.079 --> 03:01.282
YOU CAME TO THE RIGHT PLACE.

03:01.382 --> 03:04.218
YOU KNOW WHAT, BERG?
I LIKE THE CUT OF YOUR JIB.

03:04.318 --> 03:05.986
UH, THANK YOU
VERY MUCH, CAPTAIN.
I APPRECIATE THAT.

03:06.086 --> 03:09.122
CHERYL AND HER LAWYER
ARE GOING TO BE HERE
IN A MATTER OF MINUTES.

03:09.223 --> 03:12.426
YOU DON'T HAVE TO, BUT IT MIGHT
NOT BE A BAD IDEA FOR YOU TO
STICK AROUND FOR THAT MEETING.

03:12.526 --> 03:16.464
- NO, I'M GONNA GO.
- OKAY, FAIR ENOUGH.
OKAY.

03:16.564 --> 03:18.632
- YOU'RE WELCOME TO STAY.
- I LIKE THIS DESK.

03:18.732 --> 03:21.068
- YOU HAVE A LOT
OF ROOM UNDER HERE.
- YEAH, IT'S NICE.

03:21.168 --> 03:22.870
IT'D BE A GOOD DESK
TO GET BLOWJOBS UNDER.

03:22.970 --> 03:26.206
THAT'S NOT WHY I BOUGHT IT,
BUT LET'S CALL IT
A HAPPY ACCIDENT.

03:26.307 --> 03:30.344
- OKAY, BERG.
- LARRY, DON'T WORRY SO MUCH.

03:30.444 --> 03:31.879
- IT'S A GOOD DEAL.
- OKAY, I'M NOT GOING TO WORRY.

03:31.979 --> 03:33.914
I'M GONNA LEAVE IT
IN YOUR HANDS.
I TRUST YOU.

03:34.014 --> 03:35.683
- YOU SHOULD.
- I HAVE A LOT
OF CONFIDENCE IN YOU.

03:35.783 --> 03:38.218
- ALL RIGHT, SEE YOU, LARRY.
- SEE YOU AROUND.

03:38.919 --> 03:40.754
Cheryl: LARRY.

03:40.854 --> 03:43.391
- OH HEY.
- HI.

03:43.491 --> 03:46.294
- HEY. GOOD TO SEE YOU.
- HELLO.

03:46.394 --> 03:48.396
- GOOD TO SEE YOU.
- THIS IS DAVID RABINOWITZ,

03:48.496 --> 03:49.763
MY ATTORNEY.
THIS IS LARRY DAVID.

03:49.863 --> 03:51.231
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
- NICE TO MEET YOU.

03:51.332 --> 03:53.233
YOU HIRED A BALD MAN, HUH?

03:53.334 --> 03:56.704
UH, THAT WAS
A COINCIDENCE.

03:56.804 --> 03:58.406
I DIDN'T REALLY GO
AFTER A BALD MAN.

03:58.506 --> 04:01.575
YOU KNOW, YOU SHOULD
HAVE RECUSED YOURSELF.

04:01.675 --> 04:03.677
WE CAN'T GO UP
AGAINST EACH OTHER.

04:03.777 --> 04:05.746
- IT'S A CODE.
IT'S IN THE BALD CODE.
- IS IT?

04:05.846 --> 04:09.149
- YES, IT IS.
- OH, I DO NEED TO COME BY
AND PICK UP SOME STUFF.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.485
- OH, YOU WANT TO GET
THE BEDDING AND EVERYTHING?
- YES.

04:11.585 --> 04:13.421
I'M GIVING HER
THE BEDDING.
SEE?

04:13.521 --> 04:15.656
- YOU DON'T LIKE THE BEDDING.
- I LIKE THE BEDDING.

04:15.756 --> 04:17.725
AND THE PILLOWS.
I'M GIVING YOU
ALL THOSE PILLOWS.

04:17.825 --> 04:20.628
- YEAH, YOU LIKE--
YOU WANT THAT, RIGHT?
- YEAH, BUT

04:20.728 --> 04:22.696
YOU DON'T LIKE
THOSE PILLOWS EITHER.

04:22.796 --> 04:25.833
I KNOW, BUT I COULD
CHARGE YOU FOR THEM
IF I WASN'T BEING FAIR.

04:25.933 --> 04:28.469
- YOU COULD CHARGE ME
FOR THE PILLOWS?
- YES, ISN'T THAT RIGHT?

04:28.569 --> 04:30.571
- I'M NOT SURE.
- TECHNICALLY.

04:30.671 --> 04:32.473
TECHNICALLY.
CORRECT, OKAY?

04:32.573 --> 04:34.875
- OKAY.
- YOUR BALD LAWYER
SAYS TECHNICALLY YES.

04:34.975 --> 04:38.879
AND I CAN CALL YOU BALD.
IT'S LIKE BLACK PEOPLE
CALLING EACH OTHER NIGGA.

04:38.979 --> 04:41.749
- "HEY, BALDY," YOU KNOW?
- OKAY, LET'S-- IT'S BETTER
IF YOU DON'T.

04:41.849 --> 04:43.651
- OKAY.
- I THINK YOU'RE
CROSSING BOUNDARIES

04:43.751 --> 04:45.519
- THAT SHOULDN'T BE CROSSED.
- OKAY.

04:47.020 --> 04:50.558
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- I'M PRACTICING A TIC
I'M WORKING ON.

04:52.360 --> 04:55.629
YOU KNOW, FOR DATING.
I'M JUST WONDERING IF SHE'LL
POINT IT OUT, THAT'S ALL.

04:55.729 --> 04:57.731
AND THAT'S WHAT YOU DO
ON YOUR DATES?

04:57.831 --> 04:59.733
- YEAH, I'LL JUST
KEEP GOING LIKE THIS.
- YOU MAKE UP A TIC

04:59.833 --> 05:01.935
- TO SEE HOW LONG YOUR--
OKAY, UM...
- YEAH.

05:02.035 --> 05:06.540
WHAT WOULD YOU THINK IF
YOU WERE SITTING ACROSS FROM
SOMEBODY GOING LIKE THIS?

05:06.640 --> 05:08.676
IF HE WAS DOING IT
ON PURPOSE, I WOULD THINK
HE WAS AN ASSHOLE.

05:08.776 --> 05:11.379
ONLY BECAUSE I TOLD YOU
BECAUSE YOU KNOW WHO I AM.

05:11.479 --> 05:13.847
BUT IF YOU DIDN'T KNOW ME
AND WE HAD JUST MET,

05:13.947 --> 05:16.984
AND THEN ALL OF A SUDDEN
YOU'RE SITTING ACROSS
FROM ME AND I'M GOING--

05:17.084 --> 05:19.420
OKAY, THAT DOESN'T WORK.
I DON'T THINK YOU SHOULD
DO THAT.

05:19.520 --> 05:21.689
( chuckles )
WH-- WHY NOT?
HUH?

05:21.789 --> 05:23.691
- LET'S GO.
- IT'S JUST A SOCIAL EXPERIMENT.

05:23.791 --> 05:25.593
- Cheryl: I'LL TEXT YOU.
- ALL RIGHT, NICE TO MEET YOU.

05:25.693 --> 05:27.628
Rabinowitz:
NICE MEETING YOU.

05:27.728 --> 05:30.764
Larry:
I GOT THE SHARPEST
JEWISH DIVORCE LAWYER IN TOWN.

05:30.864 --> 05:32.800
- HE'S TERRIFIC.
- Jeff: YOU LIKE BERG?

05:32.900 --> 05:35.268
- I LIKE HIM A LOT, YEAH.
- OH, YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU AND I EVER SPLIT UP,

05:35.369 --> 05:37.304
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING,
WE GET A DIVORCE,

05:37.405 --> 05:39.673
50-50.
YOU TAKE WHATEVER
50% YOU WANT.

05:39.773 --> 05:41.642
I'LL TAKE WHAT'S LEFT.
NO ARGUING,

05:41.742 --> 05:44.678
- NO NEGATIVITY.
- WHAT, ARE YOU FUCKING
KIDDING ME?

05:44.778 --> 05:47.581
YOU THINK WE'RE GONNA HAVE
A NICE DIVORCE IF WE
EVER GET DIVORCED?

05:47.681 --> 05:50.584
NO FUCKING WAY.
I'M TAKING YOU FOR
EVERYTHING YOU HAVE, MISTER.

05:50.684 --> 05:53.821
I'M TAKING YOUR BALLS
AND I'M THUMBTACKING
THEM TO THE WALL.

05:53.921 --> 05:56.757
YOU'RE GONNA GET NOTHING
OUT OF IT. YOU MENTION
THE "D" WORD ONCE

05:56.857 --> 05:59.627
IN YOUR FUCKING LIFE,
YOU'LL RUE THE DAY
YOU EVER MET ME.

06:06.333 --> 06:09.470
OKAY.
I'VE GOT SOME
GREAT NEWS.

06:09.570 --> 06:12.940
GUESS WHERE THE FUNKMAN
IS GOING FOR THREE WEEKS.

06:13.040 --> 06:15.476
- MIAMI?
- LONDON!

06:15.576 --> 06:17.110
- LONDON!
- OH AH!

06:17.210 --> 06:20.113
- HOW ABOUT THAT?
- ON BUSINESS, HOW GREAT
IS THAT?

06:20.213 --> 06:21.482
- WOW, THAT'S FUN.
- ARE YOU GOING?

06:21.582 --> 06:23.451
- NO.
- OH, REALLY?

06:23.551 --> 06:26.286
- SHE DOESN'T LIKE TO TRAVEL.
- I DON'T GO ON BUSINESS TRIPS
WITH HIM.

06:26.386 --> 06:28.188
- HAVE YOU EVER BEEN THERE?
- NO.

06:28.288 --> 06:31.525
OH MY GOD, YOU SHOULD GO.
IT'S REALLY BEAUTIFUL
THIS TIME OF YEAR.

06:31.625 --> 06:34.394
- HMM, REALLY?
- YEAH!

06:34.495 --> 06:36.196
- LONDON!
- MAYBE I SHOULD GO, MARTY.

06:36.296 --> 06:38.832
NO, IT'S COLD.
RIGHT NOW IT'S COLD
AND FOGGY AND DANGEROUS.

06:38.932 --> 06:41.702
THEY HAVE GANGS OVER THERE
AND EVERYTHING ELSE AND I'LL
BE DOING BUSINESS.

06:41.802 --> 06:44.505
I NEVER TRAVEL WITH YOU.
I THINK IT'S A GREAT IDEA.
I'M GOING.

06:44.605 --> 06:47.040
- LET'S TALK ABOUT--
- THANK YOU.

06:47.140 --> 06:49.543
THAT'S DECIDED.
I'M IN.

06:51.879 --> 06:53.514
UM...

06:53.614 --> 06:56.149
- WHAT'S EVERYBODY
GETTING FOR LUNCH?
- FISH CHOWDER.

06:56.249 --> 06:58.118
GONNA HAVE SOME SORT
OF LIGHT SALAD.

06:58.218 --> 07:00.420
- I'M NOT THAT HUNGRY.
- I THINK I'M GONNA
GET THE BUFFET.

07:00.521 --> 07:03.223
- ALL RIGHT.
- ALL RIGHT.
I'LL BE BACK.

07:03.323 --> 07:05.693
- THE FISH CHOWDER'S YUMMY.
- LARRY!

07:05.793 --> 07:07.561
- HEY, JOE.
- LARRY, HOW ARE YOU?

07:07.661 --> 07:09.162
- PRETTY GOOD.
- Susie: ANNA!

07:09.262 --> 07:11.264
- OH MY GOD, HOW ARE YOU?
- RIGHT RIGHT RIGHT,
THIS IS ANNA.

07:11.364 --> 07:14.034
HEY, THIS IS--
YOU KNOW JOE O'DONNELL,
THE OWNER OF THE DODGERS.

07:14.134 --> 07:16.203
- YES.
- HI, EVERYBODY.
I DIDN'T WANT TO INTERRUPT.

07:16.303 --> 07:18.271
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
- ANNA AND I DID PILATES
TOGETHER.

07:18.371 --> 07:20.641
- HOW ARE YOU?
THINGS GOING GOOD?
- GREAT GREAT, YEAH.

07:20.741 --> 07:22.810
DID YOU SPEAK TO ANDY TODAY?
OUR FEARLESS ATTORNEY?

07:22.910 --> 07:25.378
- WE HAVE THE SAME
DIVORCE LAWYER.
- OH YES!

07:25.479 --> 07:27.247
OH, THE FUN
WE'RE HAVING.

07:27.347 --> 07:29.817
- HOW'S IT GOING WITH YOU?
- WELL...

07:29.917 --> 07:32.219
YOU KNOW,
IT'S COMPLICATED
TO SAY THE LEAST.

07:32.319 --> 07:35.422
THE TEAM IS--
THE TEAM'S AN ASSET

07:35.523 --> 07:37.758
AND IT'S KIND OF A LITTLE
PRECARIOUS RIGHT NOW.

07:37.858 --> 07:40.427
I THINK HE'LL
COME THROUGH FOR US THOUGH.
I'M PRETTY CONFIDENT.

07:40.528 --> 07:42.295
- YEAH, HE'S GOOD.
- BY THE WAY, WOULD YOU BE...

07:42.395 --> 07:44.832
WOULD YOU BE INTERESTED
IN COMING OUT, SITTING
IN A BOX WITH ME?

07:44.932 --> 07:46.634
- OH, THAT'D BE FUN.
- WE CAN COMMISERATE,

07:46.734 --> 07:49.069
DISCUSS WHY THE HELL WE GOT
MARRIED IN THE FIRST PLACE.

07:49.169 --> 07:51.271
YEAH, I'D BE
INTERESTED.

07:51.371 --> 07:53.373
- YES.
- OH, WE SHOULD TELL THEM.

07:53.473 --> 07:57.978
JOE'S 13-YEAR-OLD DAUGHTER
KYRA IS GOING TO BE KNOCKING
ON YOUR DOORS POSSIBLY.

07:58.078 --> 08:00.480
- LOOK OUT!
- SHE'S SELLING
GIRL SCOUT COOKIES.

08:00.581 --> 08:02.716
- IT'S THE LAST WEEK.
- SHE'S GOING FOR THE RECORD
THIS YEAR.

08:02.816 --> 08:04.885
- SHE WAS CLOSE.
- WE'RE IN, RIGHT, JEFF?

08:04.985 --> 08:07.555
I'LL BE SLAMMING THE DOOR
IN HER FACE. I HOPE THAT
DOESN'T BOTHER YOU.

08:07.655 --> 08:09.723
- OH COME ON, GIVE HER A BREAK.
- WE'RE SENDING HER
TO YOU FIRST.

08:09.823 --> 08:11.091
SHE'S COMING.
BE PREPARED.

08:11.191 --> 08:13.594
- TAKE CARE, EVERYBODY.
- NICE TO SEE YOU.

08:17.565 --> 08:19.700
- OH, OKAY!
- HUH?

08:19.800 --> 08:21.234
- THERE YOU GO.
- YOU LOVING THAT?

08:21.334 --> 08:24.605
- THAT IS BEAUTIFUL.
- I TOLD YOU THE BUFFET, MAN.

08:24.705 --> 08:26.874
- BOY, DID WE DO
THE WRONG THING.
- SHRIMP?

08:26.974 --> 08:30.878
- CRAB LEGS, SHRIMP, POTATOES.
- I'M STILL A LITTLE BIT HUNGRY.
CAN I TAKE A COUPLE POTATOES?

08:30.978 --> 08:32.646
- HELP YOURSELF.
- Funkhouser: LOOK AT THAT.

08:32.746 --> 08:34.514
- TAKE A CRAB LEG.
ABSOLUTELY.
- ARE YOU SURE?

08:34.615 --> 08:37.217
- TAKE SOME SHRIMP TOO.
- I'LL TAKE TWO SHRIMP.
THERE WE GO.

08:37.317 --> 08:38.719
- THANK YOU.
- TAKE THREE.
YOU WANT THREE?

08:38.819 --> 08:40.754
NO, TWO'S PLENTY.
THAT'S ALL I WANT.

08:40.854 --> 08:44.524
- Funkhouser: WHEN YOU
GO BACK, GET ME SOME.
- HI, I'M SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

08:44.625 --> 08:47.561
UM, BUT YOU CAN'T TAKE
FROM THE BUFFET

08:47.661 --> 08:49.763
AND SHARE WITH SOMEONE
WHO'S ORDERED OFF THE MENU.

08:49.863 --> 08:53.200
SO UNFORTUNATELY WE'RE
GOING TO HAVE TO CHARGE YOU
FOR AN ADDITIONAL BUFFET.

08:53.300 --> 08:55.335
- IT SAYS IT'S ALL YOU CAN EAT.
- IT'S ALL YOU CAN EAT.

08:55.435 --> 08:57.738
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE
IF I GIVE IT TO
SOMEBODY ELSE?

08:57.838 --> 08:59.740
BECAUSE THEN HE'S EATING IT.
IT'S ALL HE CAN EAT ALSO.

08:59.840 --> 09:03.543
I WASN'T GOING TO MAKE
A SECOND VISIT. THIS IS IT.
THIS IS MY ONLY PLATE.

09:03.644 --> 09:06.546
- BUT HOW AM I TO KNOW THAT?
- IT DOESN'T SAY THAT
YOU CAN'T--

09:06.647 --> 09:09.016
EXCUSE ME, MAYBE I CAN HELP.
HELLO, I'M HIRIAM KATZ,

09:09.116 --> 09:11.752
ATTORNEY-AT-LAW.
MAYBE I CAN STRAIGHTEN
THIS OUT.

09:11.852 --> 09:14.454
FIRST OF ALL, IN YOUR IMPLIED
CONTRACT WITH THIS MAN

09:14.554 --> 09:17.524
THERE IS NOTHING THAT
ALLOWS YOU TO RESTRICT WHAT HE
DOES WITH YOUR PRODUCT

09:17.625 --> 09:20.594
AFTER HE PURCHASES IT,
SO HE CAN DO WHATEVER HE WANTS
WITH THE FOOD.

09:20.694 --> 09:24.131
AND SECONDLY, IF YOU SUSPECT
THAT HE'S STEALING ANOTHER
BUFFET FROM YOU,

09:24.231 --> 09:26.466
YOU'D HAVE TO BE ABLE
TO ESTABLISH PRIOR INTENT.

09:26.566 --> 09:28.335
NOW CAN YOU PROVE
PRIOR INTENT?

09:28.435 --> 09:30.303
I DIDN'T THINK SO.

09:30.403 --> 09:33.340
SO IN THE ABSENCE OF THAT,
I'M AFRAID THERE'S REALLY
NOTHING YOU CAN DO

09:33.440 --> 09:36.810
EXCEPT PROBABLY APOLOGIZE
TO THESE PEOPLE AND MAYBE
BUY THEM A ROUND OF DRINKS.

09:36.910 --> 09:38.946
HMM?

09:40.280 --> 09:42.049
I'M SORRY AND...

09:42.149 --> 09:44.818
I'D BE HAPPY TO GET YOU
A ROUND OF DRINKS.

09:44.918 --> 09:46.720
APOLOGY ACCEPTED.
THAT WON'T BE NECESSARY.

09:46.820 --> 09:48.355
- THANK YOU.
- THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

09:48.455 --> 09:51.258
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.
I HATE TO SEE PEOPLE
RIPPED OFF THAT WAY.

09:51.358 --> 09:53.761
SO I THOUGHT I WOULD DIVE IN.
I AM HIRIAM KATZ,

09:53.861 --> 09:55.629
ATTORNEY-AT-LAW.
HERE'S MY CARD.

09:55.729 --> 09:58.331
ENJOY YOUR BRUNCH.

10:02.169 --> 10:04.571
HEY, HOW ABOUT O'DONNELL
INVITING ME TO SIT IN HIS BOX?

10:04.672 --> 10:06.173
THAT'S SOME COOL SHIT.
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.

10:06.273 --> 10:07.941
- THIS IS GONNA BE
GREAT FOR US, MAN.
- I KNOW.

10:08.041 --> 10:09.910
THIS IS BETTER THAN--
EXCUSE ME?

10:10.010 --> 10:11.544
- IT'S GREAT FOR US.
- GREAT FOR US?

10:11.645 --> 10:14.281
- IT'S GREAT FOR ME.
- THE HOOKUP ALWAYS COMES
WITH A PLUS ONE.

