OF THESE AND I'M REALLY
FRUSTRATED RIGHT NOW.

13:04.484 --> 13:06.719
OH, OKAY!

13:06.820 --> 13:08.555
I GOT IT.
I GOT IT.

13:08.655 --> 13:10.757
LOOK, IT PUSHES IT OUT.

13:10.858 --> 13:13.861
- ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE READING
THE RIGHT DIRECTIONS?
- NO, LISTEN TO ME.

13:13.961 --> 13:16.763
LISTEN TO ME.
TAKE THE INSIDE WHERE
THE STRING IS

13:16.864 --> 13:19.232
AND PUSH IT--
PUSH IT.

13:19.332 --> 13:21.701
- PUSH IT?
- PUSH IT.
YOU'LL SEE A COTTON--

13:21.801 --> 13:24.337
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
- YOU'LL SEE A COTTON PIECE
COME OUT.

13:24.437 --> 13:25.973
OKAY, THAT DOESN'T
MAKE ANY SENSE.

13:26.073 --> 13:27.607
- CAN YOU TALK
A LITTLE SLOWER?
- OKAY.

13:27.707 --> 13:29.409
- THERE'S A TUBE, RIGHT?
- YES.

13:29.509 --> 13:31.211
- THERE'S AN OUTER TUBE
AND AN INNER TUBE.
- INNER TUBE?

13:31.311 --> 13:33.546
PUT THE OUTER TUBE
IN YOUR VAGINA.

13:33.646 --> 13:37.084
- AND-AND--
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M DOING.
I'VE NEVER DONE THIS BEFORE.

13:37.184 --> 13:39.152
TAKE THE--

13:39.252 --> 13:42.355
TAKE THE OUTER TUBE,
TAKE YOUR THUMB AND
MIDDLE FINGER...

13:42.455 --> 13:45.558
- WAIT, WHAT?
- ...AND PUSH THAT TUBE
FORWARD.

13:45.658 --> 13:48.561
- IT COMES OUT OF THE PLASTIC!
- WAIT, THAT SEEMS WRONG.

13:48.661 --> 13:51.865
LOOK, IT CAME
OUT OF THE PLASTIC.
I'M HOLDING IT!

13:51.965 --> 13:54.167
- OKAY--
- YOU GOT IT?

13:54.267 --> 13:56.236
I THINK SO.
I THINK I GOT IT.

13:56.336 --> 13:57.537
ALL RIGHT!

14:16.623 --> 14:18.725
Larry:
SO I'M AT A LIGHT ON BUNDY
AND SAN VINCENTE,

14:18.825 --> 14:20.427
GUY PULLS UP NEXT TO ME
ON A MOTORCYCLE,

14:20.527 --> 14:23.363
- GUESS WHO IT TURNS OUT TO BE.
- PORTIA DE ROSSI.

14:23.463 --> 14:24.898
- HUH-UH.
- WHO?

14:24.998 --> 14:27.300
- ANDREW BERG, MY LAWYER.
- REALLY? ON A MOTORCYCLE?

14:27.400 --> 14:29.602
YEAH.
WHAT IS A JEW DOING
ON A MOTORCYCLE?

14:29.702 --> 14:32.405
I NEVER RECALL EVER SEEING
A JEW ON A MOTORCYCLE.

14:32.505 --> 14:35.575
- DID YOU EVER WANT
TO GET A MOTORCYCLE?
- I ONCE GOT ON A MOTOR SCOOTER

14:35.675 --> 14:37.177
AND GOT ABOUT 30 FEET
AND FELL.

14:37.277 --> 14:39.312
- MOTOR SCOOTER?
WHEN DID THIS OCCUR?
- I WAS IN COLLEGE.

14:39.412 --> 14:40.981
- OH, YOU WERE IN COLLEGE.
- YEAH.

14:41.081 --> 14:42.715
SO YOU HAD A BIG 'FRO
ON A MOTOR SCOOTER?

14:42.815 --> 14:45.752
- YES, YEAH.
- IT'S NOT THIS LARRY
ON THE MOTOR SCOOTER.

14:45.852 --> 14:48.055
IT'S YOUNG LARRY
WITH THE BIG 'FRO.

14:48.155 --> 14:50.190
RIGHT, IT'S 'FRO LARRY.
'FRO--

14:50.290 --> 14:54.027
WELL, GOOD AFTERNOON,
GENERAL PETRAEUS.
IT'S LOVELY TO SEE YOU.

14:54.127 --> 14:55.929
- FUNNY FUNNY FUNNY.
- ( giggles )

14:56.029 --> 14:58.165
- AND I THANK YOU
FOR YOUR SERVICE.
- HA HA HA HA.

14:58.265 --> 15:00.233
THIS HAPPENS
TO BE VERY IN.
JOHN VARVATOS...

15:00.333 --> 15:02.335
- REALLY?
- ...HIS ENTIRE
FALL COLLECTION...

15:02.435 --> 15:04.537
- IS THAT RIGHT? CAMOUFLAGE,
IS THAT THE NEW THING?
- ...IS CAMOUFLAGE.

15:04.637 --> 15:06.473
YES.
LISTEN, YOU KNOW,
I GOTTA TELL YOU SOMETHING.

15:06.573 --> 15:08.942
YOU BETTER GO
OVER TO O'DONNELL
AND APOLOGIZE.

15:09.042 --> 15:12.345
- WHY, WHAT DID I DO?
- YOU'RE TEACHING HIS DAUGHTER
HOW TO PUT IN A TAMPON?

15:12.445 --> 15:14.847
- HE'S VERY UPSET ABOUT IT.
- OH, COME ON!

15:14.948 --> 15:16.549
IF HER NOSE IS RUNNING
AND SHE NEEDED A TISSUE,

15:16.649 --> 15:18.518
I WOULD HAVE
GIVEN HER A TISSUE.
SAME THING.

15:18.618 --> 15:20.887
NO, NOT THE SAME THING.
IT'S INAPPROPRIATE.

15:20.988 --> 15:22.956
- IT'S A TAMPON.
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

15:23.056 --> 15:26.193
- THE GIRL WAS HAVING
HER PERIOD IN MY HOUSE.
- IT'S NOT MY ISSUE, LARRY!

15:26.293 --> 15:28.328
IT'S HIS ISSUE.
I'M JUST THE MESSENGER.

15:28.428 --> 15:30.363
DON'T KILL THE MESSENGER,
AS THEY SAY.

15:30.463 --> 15:32.665
- I WOULDN'T MIND
KILLING THE MESSENGER.
- YEAH, I BET.

15:32.765 --> 15:34.767
- ( doorbell rings )
- SAY THOSE THINGS WHEN
YOU REALLY LOVE ME.

15:34.867 --> 15:36.836
- I THINK THE WHOLE
THING IS CRAZY.
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

15:36.936 --> 15:39.339
- I DON'T THINK HE'S GONNA
GIVE YOU THOSE TICKETS.
- REALLY?

15:39.439 --> 15:41.674
- THAT'S SO RIDICULOUS.
- SO GO APOLOGIZE.

15:41.774 --> 15:44.577
- WHAT'S THE BIG FUCKING DEAL?
- I'M GONNA GO OVER THERE
AND TALK TO HIM.

15:44.677 --> 15:47.447
- HI, MARTY.
- HI, SUSIE.

15:47.547 --> 15:50.583
WELL, LOOK WHO'S HERE.
IT'S THE BIG FUNK.

15:50.683 --> 15:52.419
YOU ARE A COLOSSAL PRICK.

15:52.519 --> 15:54.421
- ( laughs )
- DO YOU KNOW THAT?

15:54.521 --> 15:57.057
- BOY, I'M REALLY
GETTING IT TODAY.
- YOU THINK IT'S FUNNY?

15:57.157 --> 15:58.925
- WHAT DID I DO?
- LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.

15:59.026 --> 16:01.861
YOU RUINED
MY WHOLE VACATION.
YOU HAD TO BUTT IN

16:01.961 --> 16:03.496
AND TELL NAN
TO GO ON MY TRIP.

16:03.596 --> 16:05.999
- I'M SORRY.
- I COULD HAVE
HAD THREE WEEKS

16:06.099 --> 16:08.068
WORKING
AND BEING ALONE.

16:08.168 --> 16:10.237
I WAS CURIOUS AS TO WHY
SHE WASN'T GOING.

16:10.337 --> 16:12.305
WHY DON'T YOU JUST GO WITH HER?
WHY DON'T YOU BRING HER?

16:12.405 --> 16:14.874
I'M BORED!
EVERYWHERE I GO WITH HER
WE DON'T LOOK AT EACH OTHER,

16:14.974 --> 16:17.110
SHE TALKS OVER ME.
I WANT TO BE ALONE.

16:17.210 --> 16:19.346
I WANT TO GET THE CHANCE
TO SPREAD MY WINGS.

16:19.446 --> 16:22.415
- WHY DON'T YOU GET A DIVORCE?
- I'M TOO LAZY.

16:29.022 --> 16:32.025
COMING!
YES, MAY I HELP YOU?

16:32.125 --> 16:34.094
I'M HERE TO SEE
MR. O'DONNELL.

16:34.194 --> 16:36.896
- LARRY DAVID.
- MR. O'DONNELL HERE,

16:36.996 --> 16:40.967
BUT HE GIVE ME
SPECIAL INSTRUCTION
NOT TO OPEN THE DOOR FOR YOU.

16:41.068 --> 16:42.569
WHAT?
WAIT A SECOND.

16:42.669 --> 16:45.105
WHAT DO YOU MEAN HE
DOESN'T WANT TO SEE ME?
WHY?

16:45.205 --> 16:47.874
MR. O'DONNELL SAY YOU DID
BAD THING TO MISS KYRA.

16:47.974 --> 16:49.742
- A BAD THING?
- YES.

16:49.842 --> 16:51.344
OH NO NO NO NO NO.

16:51.444 --> 16:53.646
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING BAD
TO MISS KYRA.

16:53.746 --> 16:57.016
I CLOSE DOOR.
MR. O'DONNELL SAY, "LARRY DAVID,
CLOSE DOOR ON HIM."

16:57.117 --> 16:58.585
WHAT? HOLD IT.
WAIT A SECOND.

16:58.685 --> 17:00.653
I'M SUPPOSED TO GO
TO THE BASEBALL GAME
WITH HIM.

17:00.753 --> 17:03.323
- YOU HAVE TICKET?
- NO, BUT HE ASKED ME
IF I WAS INTERESTED

17:03.423 --> 17:05.125
AND I SAID I'D BE
VERY INTERESTED.

17:05.225 --> 17:07.060
INTERESTED DOESN'T
MEAN TICKET.

17:07.160 --> 17:08.795
YEAH, INTERESTED
MEANS TICKET!

17:08.895 --> 17:10.863
I'M INTERESTED,
I HAVE NO TICKET.

17:10.963 --> 17:13.166
GARDENER INTERESTED,
CHAUFFER INTERESTED,

17:13.266 --> 17:15.435
COOK INTERESTED--
COOK MORE INTERESTED THAN ME,

17:15.535 --> 17:17.470
HE HAS NO TICKET!

17:24.010 --> 17:25.512
- Larry: NO.
- I CAN'T HAVE THEM?

17:25.612 --> 17:27.180
- NO.
- THAT'S WHERE YOU
DRAW THE LINE?

17:27.280 --> 17:29.149
- I LOVE THOSE.
- NO.

17:29.249 --> 17:30.783
WHAT?
PUT THOSE BACK.

17:30.883 --> 17:33.420
YOU DON'T EVEN
KNOW WHAT THEY ARE.
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THEY ARE?

17:33.520 --> 17:35.788
I DON'T CARE.
YOU'RE NOT COMING UP HERE
AND STEALING THOSE!

17:35.888 --> 17:37.590
- THOSE THINGS.
- YES.

17:37.690 --> 17:41.361
WELL, OKAY, IF YOU CHANGE
YOUR MIND, LET ME KNOW
AND I'LL...

17:41.461 --> 17:43.663
- I WILL, I'LL LET YOU KNOW.
- ...I WILL RETURN THEM
IMMEDIATELY.

17:43.763 --> 17:47.467
- I'LL LET YOU KNOW.
- I KNOW, IT'S KINDA WEIRD
WE'RE GONNA ACTUALLY

17:47.567 --> 17:50.203
- SIGN THE PAPERS, RIGHT?
- YEAH, WE'RE GONNA SIGN
THOSE PAPERS.

17:50.303 --> 17:53.240
- I'M FINE WITH IT.
- YOU KNOW, A LOT OF PEOPLE,
AFTER THEY GET DIVORCED,

17:53.340 --> 17:55.308
THEY LOOK AT THEIR MARRIAGE
LIKE IT WAS A WASTE OF TIME?

17:55.408 --> 17:57.009
- I DON'T THINK SO.
- I DON'T EITHER.

17:57.110 --> 17:58.978
TO ME, IT'S KIND OF
LIKE PUBLIC SCHOOL.

17:59.078 --> 18:00.947
YOU WENT TO SCHOOL,
YOU GOT THROUGH IT

18:01.047 --> 18:03.350
- AND NOW YOU MOVE ON.
- WHAT'D YOU LEARN?

18:03.450 --> 18:05.752
I WOULDN'T BE TONGUE SCRAPING
IF IT WASN'T FOR YOU.

18:05.852 --> 18:09.021
- LOOK WHAT YOU TAUGHT ME.
- AND THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE TAKING
AWAY FROM OUR MARRIAGE.

18:09.122 --> 18:12.259
- YES.
- OKAY, I'M GLAD YOU'RE
TAKING SOMETHING WITH YOU.

18:12.359 --> 18:14.294
- HEY, BEFORE YOU GO.
- YES?

18:14.394 --> 18:16.196
DO YOU THINK
THERE'S ANY CHANCE
WE COULD HAVE SEX?

18:16.296 --> 18:18.498
- UM, NO.
- COME ON.

18:18.598 --> 18:20.867
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?
HONESTLY, THINK ABOUT IT,

18:20.967 --> 18:23.270
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?
LET'S JUST DO IT.
COME ON.

18:23.370 --> 18:24.837
WHAT HAVE I DONE?
NAME ONE THING I'VE DONE

18:24.937 --> 18:26.873
THAT MAKES YOU THINK I WANT
TO HAVE SEX WITH YOU.

18:26.973 --> 18:28.975
- WELL, UM...
- I'M TALKING TO YOU?

18:29.075 --> 18:30.810
YES, YOU'RE TALKING TO ME.

18:30.910 --> 18:33.446
- THAT'S ALL YOU NEED?
- YEAH. WHEN THERE ARE WOMEN
IN THIS BEDROOM,

18:33.546 --> 18:36.015
IT SEEMS CRAZY IF
I DON'T AT LEAST OFFER.

18:36.115 --> 18:38.418
OH, I MEANT TO TELL YOU--
THIS IS INTERESTING--

18:38.518 --> 18:40.420
- YOU KNOW YOUR ATTORNEY?
- ANDREW BERG!

18:40.520 --> 18:43.256
ANDREW BERG WENT
TO HIGH SCHOOL WITH JULIE

18:43.356 --> 18:45.892
AT ST. CHRISTOPHER'S.
THEY ACTUALLY SAT NEXT
TO EACH OTHER--

18:45.992 --> 18:48.795
WAIT A SECOND.
HOW COULD ANDREW BERG

18:48.895 --> 18:51.398
GO TO ST. CHRISTOPHER'S?
ISN'T THAT A CATHOLIC SCHOOL?

18:51.498 --> 18:54.100
- YEAH.
- ( doorbell rings )

18:54.201 --> 18:57.604
I SAW HIM
ON THAT MOTORCYCLE

18:57.704 --> 18:59.539
THE OTHER DAY.

19:01.941 --> 19:03.443
- OH WELL.
- Girls: HI!

19:03.543 --> 19:06.313
- GOOD AFTERNOON.
- HELLO. GOOD AFTERNOON.

19:06.413 --> 19:08.948
SO WE'RE TROOP 205
AND WE'RE HERE TO COLLECT

19:09.048 --> 19:11.117
THE MONEY
FROM THE COOKIES, MR. DAVID,

19:11.218 --> 19:13.453
THAT KYRA SAID YOU WERE
INTERESTED IN BUYING.

19:13.553 --> 19:16.989
FIRST OF ALL, I COMMEND YOU
ON THE DEMOGRAPHICS.

19:17.089 --> 19:18.625
All:
THANK YOU.

19:18.725 --> 19:22.028
A BLACK, AN ASIAN AND--
ARE YOU A JEW PERCHANCE?

19:22.128 --> 19:25.698
- UH, NO.
- OH OKAY, STILL,

19:25.798 --> 19:27.667
WONDERFUL.

19:27.767 --> 19:30.903
REGARDING THE COOKIES,
THERE'S BEEN A CHANGE
OF PLANS.

19:31.003 --> 19:34.173
SORRY TO SAY,

19:34.274 --> 19:35.708
I NO LONGER WANT THEM.

19:35.808 --> 19:38.245
BUT KYRA SAID YOU WERE
INTERESTED IN BUYING THEM.

19:38.345 --> 19:40.547
I WAS INTERESTED AND NOW,

19:40.647 --> 19:42.615
AS A RESULT
OF SOME DIFFICULTIES
WITH HER FATHER,

19:42.715 --> 19:44.784
- I'M NO LONGER INTERESTED.
- WHAT?

19:44.884 --> 19:47.220
- YOU'RE NOT GETTING
ANY MONEY FROM ME.
- YOU CAN'T DO THAT!

19:47.320 --> 19:49.522
- BE A GENTLEMAN.
- I AM A GENTLEMAN, YOUNG LADY!

19:49.622 --> 19:51.691
- OH NO, YOU'RE NOT!
- A REAL GENTLEMAN...

19:51.791 --> 19:53.993
- WOULD GIVE US THE MONEY.
- ...WOULD GIVE US
THE MONEY, YEAH.

19:54.093 --> 19:55.395
- I AM A GENTLEMAN--
- NO, YOU'RE NOT!

19:55.495 --> 19:57.196
- YES, I AM A GENTLEMAN.
- YOU CAN'T JUST DO THAT!

19:57.297 --> 19:58.498
- YES, YEAH, I'M DOING IT.
- NO!

19:58.598 --> 20:00.333
YOU GO TALK
TO JOE O'DONNELL.

20:00.433 --> 20:02.201
ASK HIM WHY THERE'S NOT
GOING TO BE ANY COOKIES!

20:02.302 --> 20:04.504
- ( girls yelling )
- OH, TOO BAD!

20:05.505 --> 20:06.539
JERK!

20:06.639 --> 20:08.675
Berg:
HEY, LOOK WHO'S HERE!

20:08.775 --> 20:10.810
- HELLO, BERG.
- HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

20:10.910 --> 20:12.745
I'M FEELING OKAY.
SO, BERG,

20:12.845 --> 20:15.448
I WAS TALKING TO CHERYL
AND SHE TOLD ME

20:15.548 --> 20:18.184
THAT A FRIEND OF HERS

20:18.285 --> 20:20.553
WENT TO HIGH SCHOOL
WITH YOU.

20:21.888 --> 20:23.356
- REALLY?
- YES.

20:23.456 --> 20:25.458
I THINK THE NAME
OF THE HIGH SCHOOL WAS...

20:25.558 --> 20:29.329
- ST.... CHRISTOPHER'S.
- ST. CHRISTOPHER'S,
THAT'S CORRECT.

20:29.429 --> 20:31.398
THAT IS MY ALMA MATER, YES.

20:31.498 --> 20:34.901
DIDN'T KNOW THAT THEY TOOK JEWS
AT ST. CHRISTOPHER'S.

20:35.001 --> 20:38.104
OH, WELL, THEY DON'T.
I MEAN, WHY WOULD THEY?

20:38.204 --> 20:40.440
- OH, I'M NOT--
I'M NOT JEWISH.
- OH!

20:40.540 --> 20:42.675
- YOU'RE NOT.
- DID YOU THINK I WAS JEWISH?

20:42.775 --> 20:45.144
